<tt>Tue Jul 29 11:42:45 US/Eastern 1997
</tt><p>
I don't think I had any &quot;real&quot; dreams when I was 14, 15, 16...  They were more or less the canned, stereotypical dreams made from what you can see out there on TV and in magazines about people's career choices:  men are the doctors and women are the nurses; or women in high-powered positions have it all (kids, husband, success) and never seem stressed out; or people with somewhat mundane/low paying jobs live in fabulous apartments and have lots of extra spending $$.  I thought maybe I'd like to be a scientist, but I didn't really have a sense of how to get there or what that really meant.  Can teenagers have dreams or expectations of their futures that are really meaningful--I don't know.
